race.description: Melbourne Chain Wire Fencing Maiden Plate
race.comment: Connections of EQUIVASTER (8) could not have hoped to find a better race for their daughter of Zoustar, who has run top three in three jumpouts this time in. Drawn wide, but she's demonstrated an ability to get out of the gates quickly when asked, so expect her to be prominent. GOOD ONYA CHAMP (5) has only placed once from six starts but comes through stronger races than this and looks the best of the raced brigade. SIRSA NUWA (11) faced the starter for the first time and finished fifth last start at Stawell over 1100m, beaten 3 lengths, but will be better for that, draws well and will appreciate the extra 100m. BRAZEN FLING (6) needs to lift on the past two sixth placings, but placed at her first three runs of the prep and is a key player if she can rediscover that form.
